The issue of some validators having issues setting weights is due to the datalog growing to an unsustainable size. To reduce the load of this we are pruning the datalog to the last 50 days of data, this is not effecting network model performance nor weights of most miners significantly.

There are new miners getting incentives, there are validators functioning, I can see payloads are not being dropped 98+% of the time,  the network model is increasing in accuracy. This network processes somewhere in the realm of 42,752,000 embeddings per day. As a result there are and will continue to be very high CPU and RAM usages. 

In the future when validator outages and issues occur do not @ individiual validators.

I will also note: The need for 256 gigs of RAM has been outdated for > 30 days. As I announced here: https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1384252267770806293/1411668287795892244 as well as in the private communications with you.
